PAM Configuration:

1) Configure ss5.pam file;

2) Linux:
	Copy ss5.pam into /etc/pam.d/ directory;
   Solaris:
	Copy ss5.pam content into /etc/pam.confi;

3) Set SS5_PAM_AUTH options in /etc/ss5/ss5.conf file.

NOTE: if using /etc/passwd like PAM authentication, you must start ss5 with "-u root" option!
